
##1. Install Maven
```sh
$ brew install maven
```
Johnny@Johnny-Mac:~$ mvn -version
Apache Maven 3.5.0 (ff8f5e7444045639af65f6095c62210b5713f426; 2017-04-03T12:39:06-07:00)
Maven home: /usr/local/Cellar/maven/3.5.0/libexec
Java version: 1.8.0_101, vendor: Oracle Corporation
Java home: /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.8.0_101.jdk/Contents/Home/jre
Default locale: en_US, platform encoding: UTF-8
OS name: "mac os x", version: "10.12.6", arch: "x86_64", family: "mac"

Step 1: Create a new folder
mkdir my-docker-test
cd my-docker-test
Step 2: Build the sample app
You could test the image with our sample app: sample-app

git clone https://github.com/Bankmonitor/sample-app .
```
cd sample-app
mvn -f pom.xml clean package
cp /target/app.jar ~/Documents/docker-springboot/app.jar
```

Step 3: Create a new Dockerfile
```sh
$ cd ~/Johnny
$ mkdir Docker
$ cd Docker
$ vim Dockerfile
```

```sh
FROM bankmonitor/spring-boot
```

Step 4: Build the new image
```sh
docker build -t spring-boot-hello:0.1 .
```

Step 5: Run the new image
docker run --name=boothello -v ~/Documents/docker-springboot:/app/ -p 31030:8080 spring-boot-hello:0.1
Step 6: Test the app is started
The following command should return 'OK':

curl http://localhost:31030/status

